Topics:

  ordering columns:
    ordering the columns based on screening/prefix
    eg: order-0 order-md-1 order-sm-2


  Document - 
  DOM --> Document Object Model
  HTML
    | ---> HEAD
            | ---> META, TITLE 
    | ---> BODY
            | ---> P, A, DIV, H1
            
  DOM is used to manipulate based on the user interaction

  style:
    set any style prop value
  
  classlist --> list of classes for an element/tag/node
  
  setAttribute: function take attributeName and values
    set an attribute to element/node/tag
    eg: set src for an image element (imgEle) image-url --> https://flagcdn.com/w320/is.png
      imgEle.setAttribute('src', 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/is.png');

  document.createElement
    accepts tag name as string and create the tag for use
    eg: create new h1 tag with B39WETAMIL as content
      var h1Ele = document.createElement('h1');
      h1Ele.innerText = 'B39WETAMIl';

  innerHTML vs innerText

    innerHTML --> renders the string value by marking up any tags in string (<h1>String</h1>) string (as h1)
    innerText --> renders only the string value without any marking up (<h1>string</h1>) <h1>string</h1>


  appendChild vs append

    appendChild ---> takes only element as an arguement and adds as child to the calling tag
    and returns the appended tag

    append ---> takes one/more elements as arguments and adds all the arguments as child to the calling tag and returns nothing (undefined)

  
  getElementById --> why unique ID for all the nodes/elements/tags
    always returns the first element which has the id

  getElementsByClassName:
    return a htmlcollection with all the elements with passed classname

  querySelector vs querySelectorAll:

    querSelector:
      returns the first matching elements 
      eg: .common-class ---> return the first element which has classname common-class
    
    querSelectorAll:
      returns the all matching elements 
      eg: .common-class ---> return all the elements which has classname common-class
